    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "POS Fishing Tool Supervisor reported to Rig Medic for treatment",
      "Evacuation via non-medical helicopter for medical treatment",
      "Byron verbally notified BSEE Lafayette District on 07 October 2019",
      "Byron reported incident in eWell to BSEE Lafayette District",
      "BSEE Lafayette District inspectors mobilized to Enterprise 263 rig on 9 October 2019",
      "Incident investigation conducted with photographic documentation"
    ],
    "summary": "On 07 October 2019 at approximately 15:30 hours, a POS Fishing Tool Supervisor sustained a laceration to his right thumb while attempting to manipulate the sliding sleeve on a mechanical casing cutter during well operations. An air hoist was being used to apply upward pressure to release the sliding sleeve when the supervisor's right hand became pinched by the cutter. The injury required evacuation from the jack-up rig Enterprise 263 for medical treatment.",
